summary: In this context, 1,1,2-trichloroethene (TCE) is mentioned as one of the target contaminants in a study involving various chemicals, including toluene and ethanol. The relationship is primarily that TCE is categorized as a chemical contaminant being studied, but there is no detailed discussion of its specific interactions or significance compared to other chemicals mentioned. Thus, it is part of a broader group of chemicals being analyzed.
